[[Image:Armenian Catholic Patriarchate, Bzoummar, Lebanon (2).JPG|thumb|Headquarters of the Armenian Catholic Patriarchate in [[Bzoummar]], [[Lebanon]]]] '''Our Lady of Bzommar''' is a [[Marian shrine]] in [[Bzommar]] ({{lang-ar|بزمار}}), [[Lebanon]].
Bzommar is situated 36&nbsp;km northeast of [[Beirut]] at an elevation ranging between 920m and 950m above the [[Mediterranean]]. It is part of the [[qadaa|Caza]] of [[Keserwan District|Keserwan]]. Bzoummar is home to a [[monastery]] of the [[Armenian Catholic Church]] that was built in 1749, where the image of Our Lady of Bzommar is venerated.
